r view focus instead of total views 2. Core Monetization Philosophy section with: - The Buyer vs Viewer optimization framework - Content clustering strategy (4-5 video referral network) - The 30-day hot zone conversion window - Warm audience depletion problem and solution 3. DETAILED VIDEO PERFORMANCE TABLE with columns: - Video Title - Views - Revenue Generated - Dollar Per View - Product URL Promoted - Full Video Description - Key Strategy Used - Video Length Include these specific videos: - \"Copy This YouTube Strategy, It'll Blow Up Your Business\" - 128K views, film-booth.com/ytgs, RevTrack promotion - \"5 NEW AI That Just Changed YouTube Forever\" - 90K views, film-booth.com/ytgs, RevTrack promotion - \"How To Build A Profitable YouTube Channel In 30 Days\" - 24K views, film-booth.com/ytgs, RevTrack + AI bot - \"EXACTLY How To Create A $1,000,000 YouTube Strategy\" - 63K views, film-booth.com/ytgs - \"How I doubled my YouTube sales in 90 days\" - 16K views (livestream), getrevtrack.com with 30OFF code 4. Product Funnel Analysis section showing: - Primary offer: film-booth.com/ytgs (YouTube Growth System - high ticket program) - Secondary offer: getrevtrack.com (RevTrack software for tracking sales from videos) - Lead magnets: Free AI planning bots, free weekly advice via Booth Club - Price points and conversion paths 5. The 6-Step Sales System (Detailed Tactical SOP Table) with columns: - Step Number - Step Name - Tactical Action Required - Expected Input - Expected Output - Time Required - Success Metrics - Tools Needed - Ed's Specific Implementation Steps to include: Step 1: Intro Hook (3 elements in 15 seconds - problem setup, credibility proof, value promise) Step 2: Killer Insight Front-Loading (best point in first third) Step 3: Early CTA (ask for email/click in first 90 seconds) Step 4: Make Information Feel New (spreadsheets, triangles, unique frameworks) Step 5: Reminder CTA (ask 3 times: beginning, middle, end) Step 6: Strategic End Screens (point to