el) 12. Critical Success Factors (Bullet List): - Track EVERYTHING (built RevTrack software for this purpose) - Consistency over virality (10K views with high conversion > 100K views low conversion) - Niche down to ONE buyer avatar - Match channel content to offer 100% - Build referral network of 4-5 evergreen videos - Optimize for warm audience retention - Use data to drive all decisions 13. What NOT To Do section: - Don't optimize for YouTube Studio metrics - Don't appeal to broad audience for views - Don't spend 15 hours/day on production - Don't use multiple social platforms (Ed deleted all except YouTube + email) - Don't make content about 10 different things - Don't wait 3-6 months to promote (hit them in 30-day hot zone) 14. Tech Stack & Tools section: - RevTrack (sales tracking from videos) - getrevtrack.com - Nano Banana (AI thumbnail creation) - Google AI Studio (app building, scripting) - Lovable.dev (website/landing page builder) - Email automation platform - Community posts (YouTube native) 15. Key Performance Indicators Table with: - KPI Name - Ed's Target - Industry Average - How to Measure - Why It Matters Include KPIs like: - Dollar per view ($4-21 vs pennies) - Link CTR (8-10% vs 1%) - Return viewers (stable/growing) - Email signup rate (per video) - Conversion rate (clicks to sales) 16. Implementation Roadmap section with 30-60-90 day plan: - Days 1-7: Setup tracking, audit channel/offer alignment - Days 8-30: Content sprint (test multiple formats), track everything - Days 31-60: Double down on winning formats, build referral network - Days 61-90: Optimize conversion points, scale what works 17. Case Study Highlights section: - Client with 3-400 views/video hitting $100K/month (permanent jewelry niche) - Client with $64/view (extremely niche targeting) - Ed's own transition: 370K subs channel abandoned for 40K focused channel = 4x revenue - One video made $280K - One video made $178K from 400K+ views Use professional styling with: - Clean typograp